<span id="page_10">p. 10</span>

#### X

<div style="font-size: 90%">

The Ju Fên; mainly narrative. The affection of the wives on the Ju, and
their solicitude about their husbands’ honor.

</div>

<div style="margin-left: 20%; margin-right: 20%; font-size: 110%;">

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_1">1</span></span>Along the raised
banks of the Ju,  
  To hew slim stein and branch I wrought,  
My lord away, my husband true,  
  Like hunger pang my troubled thought!

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2">2</span></span>Along the raised
banks of the Ju,  
  Branch and fresh shoot confessed my art.  
I've seen my lord, my husband true,  
  And still he folds me in his heart.

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_3">3</span></span>As the toiled
bream makes red its tail,  
  Toil you, sir, for the royal house,  
Amidst its blazing fires, nor quail:—  
  Your parents see you pay your vows.

</div>

